                   "message":  "NEWPROJECT-SAVE-SUBSTRATE: rge-scene-loader writer that creates a new .rge-project tree\n\nSave-As-to-a-new-project, substrate half (mirrors #273 PROJECT-SAVE-SUBSTRATE /\n#267 SCENE-SAVE-SUBSTRATE). save_project_world_to_path only OVERWRITES an\nexisting project; this adds the create-the-tree writer. rge-scene-loader only —\nno editor-shell, no rfd, no keybinding, 0 Cargo.toml.\n\nNew pub fn save_world_as_new_project(world, project_dir)\n-\u003e Result\u003cPathBuf, NewProjectWorldSaveError\u003e:\n- folder-derived name; tree = \u003cdir\u003e/.rge-project + \u003cdir\u003e/scenes/main.rge-scene;\n  manifest defaults version V0_1_0, target_tiers [Desktop], plugins [], one\n  scene path \"scenes/main.rge-scene\".\n- no clobber: errors (before any write) if \u003cdir\u003e/.rge-project OR\n  \u003cdir\u003e/scenes/main.rge-scene already exists, so neither an existing project nor\n  a user file in a non-project folder is overwritten.\n- returns the created .rge-project path (so a caller can adopt it as the new\n  save source); the layout round-trips through load_scene_world_from_path by\n  construction.\n\nNew NewProjectWorldSaveError (NoProjectDirName / ProjectAlreadyExists /\nSceneAlreadyExists / CreateSceneDir / Scene / SerializeManifest / WriteManifest).\n\nTests (new tests/new_project_save_round_trip.rs, mirroring\nproject_save_round_trip.rs helpers): manifest-field defaults; round-trip via\nload_scene_world_from_path; existing-manifest refusal (no clobber); existing-\nscene refusal (user file byte-unchanged).\n\nDispatch B (NEWPROJECT-SAVE-WIRING) will wire NewProjectSaveDialog /\nNewProjectSaveHook, Ctrl+Shift+S, and the SaveSource::Project switch over this.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
